---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import HeroSectionComponent from '../../components/HeroSection.astro';

const title = 'HeroSection';
const description =
  'WCAG AAA compliant hero component with enhanced accessibility, responsive design, and flexible layout options for marketing sections.';
---

<DocsLayout seoTitle={title} seoDescription={description}>
  <section class="space-y-4">
    <p class="text-base text-slate-100">
      HeroSection provides a prominent, accessible hero component perfect for
      landing pages and marketing sections. Built with WCAG AAA compliance,
      semantic HTML, and comprehensive responsive design features.
    </p>
    <p class="text-base text-slate-200">
      The component features multiple visual variants, flexible sizing options,
      and intelligent content alignment for professional hero presentations.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-6">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Props</h2>
    <dl class="grid gap-6 sm:grid-cols-2">
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          title
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Main headline text for the hero section. Required.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          subtitle?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Supporting subtitle text that appears below the main headline.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          primary?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Primary call-to-action button with href, label, target, and variant
          properties.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          secondary?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Secondary call-to-action button with href, label, target, and variant
          properties.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          variant?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Visual theme: <code>default</code>, <code>gradient</code>, <code
            >minimal</code
          >, <code>dark</code>. Defaults to <code>default</code>.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          align?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Content alignment: <code>left</code>, <code>center</code>, <code
            >right</code
          >. Defaults to <code>center</code>.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          size?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Size variant: <code>sm</code>, <code>md</code>, <code>lg</code>, <code
            >xl</code
          >. Defaults to <code>lg</code>.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          headingLevel?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Semantic heading level: <code>h1</code>, <code>h2</code>, <code
            >h3</code
          >. Defaults to <code>h1</code>.
        </dd>
      </div>
    </dl>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-6">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Usage</h2>
    <div
      class="space-y-3 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/50 bg-slate-900/30 p-6"
    >
      <p class="text-sm text-slate-300">
        Import the HeroSection component and provide at minimum a title. The
        component automatically handles responsive design and accessibility
        features.
      </p>
      <pre
        class="rounded bg-slate-950/50 p-4 text-sm text-slate-300 overflow-x-auto"><code>{`---
import HeroSection from '../../components/HeroSection.astro';
---

<HeroSection
  title="Build accessible experiences faster"
  subtitle="Create beautiful, WCAG AAA compliant components with our design system."
  variant="gradient"
  size="lg"
  align="center"
  primary={{ 
    href: "/get-started", 
    label: "Get Started",
    variant: "primary" 
  }}
  secondary={{ 
    href: "/docs", 
    label: "View Documentation",
    variant: "secondary" 
  }}
/>`}</code></pre>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-6">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Examples</h2>

    <div class="space-y-8">
      <div
        class="space-y-3 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/50 bg-slate-900/30 p-6"
      >
        <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-slate-100">Default Hero</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-300">
          Standard hero section with centered content and gradient background.
        </p>
        <div class="bg-slate-800/50 rounded p-6">
          <HeroSectionComponent
            title="Build accessible experiences faster"
            subtitle="Comet Astro ships a polished component system with AAA-ready themes, focusing on speed, accessibility, and developer joy."
            primary={{ href: '#', label: 'Get started' }}
            secondary={{ href: '#', label: 'View docs' }}
          />
        </div>
      </div>

      <div
        class="space-y-3 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/50 bg-slate-900/30 p-6"
      >
        <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-slate-100">Minimal Variant</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-300">
          Clean, minimal hero with subtle styling and left-aligned content.
        </p>
        <div class="bg-slate-800/50 rounded p-6">
          <HeroSectionComponent
            title="Simple and Clean Design"
            subtitle="Sometimes less is more. This minimal variant focuses on content with subtle styling."
            variant="minimal"
            align="left"
            size="md"
            primary={{ href: '#', label: 'Learn More' }}
          />
        </div>
      </div>

      <div
        class="space-y-3 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/50 bg-slate-900/30 p-6"
      >
        <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-slate-100">Gradient Variant</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-300">
          Vibrant gradient background with enhanced visual appeal.
        </p>
        <div class="bg-slate-800/50 rounded p-6">
          <HeroSectionComponent
            title="Stunning Visual Design"
            subtitle="Eye-catching gradients that maintain WCAG AAA accessibility standards."
            variant="gradient"
            size="lg"
            primary={{ href: '#', label: 'Explore Features' }}
            secondary={{ href: '#', label: 'See Examples' }}
          />
        </div>
      </div>

      <div
        class="space-y-3 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/50 bg-slate-900/30 p-6"
      >
        <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-slate-100">Small Size</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-300">
          Compact hero perfect for secondary pages or smaller sections.
        </p>
        <div class="bg-slate-800/50 rounded p-6">
          <HeroSectionComponent
            title="Compact Hero Section"
            subtitle="Perfect for secondary pages that need a prominent but not overwhelming header."
            size="sm"
            variant="minimal"
            primary={{ href: '#', label: 'Continue' }}
          />
        </div>
      </div>

      <div
        class="space-y-3 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/50 bg-slate-900/30 p-6"
      >
        <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-slate-100">Right Aligned</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-300">
          Right-aligned content for unique layouts and design variety.
        </p>
        <div class="bg-slate-800/50 rounded p-6">
          <HeroSectionComponent
            title="Right-Aligned Content"
            subtitle="Alternative alignment options for creative layouts and design flexibility."
            align="right"
            size="md"
            primary={{ href: '#', label: 'Get Started' }}
            secondary={{ href: '#', label: 'Learn More' }}
          />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-6">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Accessibility</h2>
    <div class="space-y-4">
      <p class="text-base text-slate-200">
        The HeroSection component implements comprehensive accessibility
        features:
      </p>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-slate-300 list-disc list-inside ml-4">
        <li>
          Semantic HTML structure with proper <code>role="banner"</code> for hero
          sections
        </li>
        <li>
          WCAG AAA contrast ratios (7:1+) across all variants and color
          combinations
        </li>
        <li>Flexible heading levels (h1-h3) for proper document hierarchy</li>
        <li>
          Responsive typography that scales appropriately across all devices
        </li>
        <li>Text balancing for improved line distribution and readability</li>
        <li>ARIA labeling support with <code>ariaLabel</code> prop</li>
        <li>Focus management for interactive elements (buttons)</li>
        <li>Screen reader compatible with clear content structure</li>
        <li>
          High contrast background patterns that don't interfere with content
        </li>
        <li>Responsive spacing and layout that maintains touch targets</li>
      </ul>
      <div
        class="mt-4 rounded-lg border border-amber-500/20 bg-amber-500/10 p-4"
      >
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-200">
          <strong>Best Practice:</strong> Use <code>h1</code> for main page heroes
          and
          <code>h2</code> or <code>h3</code> for section heroes. Ensure button labels
          are descriptive and provide clear actions. Use <code>ariaLabel</code> when
          the hero represents a specific landmark on the page.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</DocsLayout>
